release.name: Minor bug fixes
release.body:
Up to this point only single bug was found (`torchdata.WrapDataset` performing infinite recursion).

This is probably the last `0.1.x` release, next version (`0.2.0`) will focus on improvements of `pipeline` related minor issues, naming and finishing documentation.

issue.title: support for pytorch 1.3.0
issue.body:
first, this is a great package! it seems like to bring the only cool part of tensorflow (tf.data) to pytorch. Thanks for the effort.

Is torch 1.3.0 supported in the current release?

comment.body:
Sorry for late reply and thanks for your interest.

Yes, it should be supported out of the box, no major changes were introduced as far as I can tell. If anything is broken due to PyTorch update, hit me up with an issue, thanks.
